avity’s Rainbow’s rockets had a paper trail."},{"number":4,"category":"character","header":"A paper bag for his son’s sake","body":"Only about ten public images of Pynchon exist — “‘Recluse’ is a code word generated by journalists,” he said, “meaning ‘doesn’t like to talk to reporters.’” But when his son Jackson loved The Simpsons, Pynchon voiced his own cameo, animated with a paper bag over his head."}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"in_law","related_id":"X3162","display_label":"was his wife’s grandfather — Justice and Nuremberg prosecutor","link_text":"Robert H. Jackson"}],"slug":"thomas-ruggles-pynchon-jr-x03232"},"HD6313":{"id":"HD6313","bio":{"display_name":"Melanie Jackson","gender":"female","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1781228992/Screenshot_2026-06-11_at_6.49.32_PM_enih71.png"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"generation_from_thomas":12},"has_descendants_documented":true,"number_of_marriages":1,"tags":["living_or_recent"],"sources":[],"birth":{},"death":{},"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X03232","children_ids":["HD6314"],"date_year":1990}],"parents":{"father_id":"I1676","mother_id":"HD6117"},"career":[{"role":"Literary agent; founder","organization":"Melanie Jackson Agency"}],"notable":{"is_notable":true,"primary_url":"https://grokipedia.com/page/Melanie_Jackson","primary_url_label":"Grokipedia","notable_blurb":"Literary agent to Pynchon and DeLillo"},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"She represents the author no one can find","body":"Melanie Jackson founded the Melanie Jackson Agency, representing a distinguished roster of authors including Nobel laureate Wole Soyinka, Pulitzer winners Ron Chernow and Steve Coll, and novelist Percival Everett. Her most famous client is the reclusive Thomas Pynchon."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Her most elusive client became her husband","body":"Jackson began representing Thomas Pynchon in the 1980s, after the famously private novelist left his longtime agent. The two married in 1990 and have guarded their privacy ever since."}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_orbit","related_id":"X3162","link_text":"Robert H. Jackson","display_label":"was her grandfather, the chief American prosecutor at Nuremberg"}],"slug":"melanie-jackson-hd6313"},"HD6314":{"id":"HD6314","bio":{"display_name":"Jackson Pynchon","gender":"male","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1781218376/images_5_qpxcgg.png"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"generation_from_thomas":13},"has_descendants_documented":false,"number_of_marriages":0,"tags":["living_or_recent"],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1991},"death":{},"marriages":[],"parents":{"father_id":"X03232","mother_id":"HD6313"},"education":[{"school_name":"Columbia University","dates":"2013","type":"undergraduate","notes":"St. Anthony Hall"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"literature","header":"He found his father’s archive a home","body":"Jackson compiled and represented the Pynchon archive in its placement at The Huntington — drawn, he said, to its aerospace and mathematics holdings and “extraordinary map collection.” The famously private novelist’s papers now sit beside rocket history."}],"slug":"jackson-pynchon-hd6314"},"X03228":{"id":"X03228","bio":{"display_name":"William Harry Chichele Pynchon","gender":"male"},"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"has_descendants_documented":true,"number_